{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, it is recommended to act at an international level against fuel theft, break-ins, and other forms of transport crime.",
    "In the development of new technology, the minimization of perceived intrusiveness should be a key design criterion, both in a direct sense (unnecessary automated braking interventions and alarms) and in an indirect sense (perceived intrusions in work flexibility and autonomy).",
    "Although truck drivers appreciate technologies that improve safety and efficiency, the feeling of autonomy being compromised indicates a need for less meddlesome technology.",
    "are relatively high among international drivers (Q4).",
    "The mean (SD) scores for Work Pressure are 0.22 (0.98) for national drivers, 0.05 (0.95) for drivers in the Benelux/Ruhr Area, and -0.23 (0.99) for international drivers."
  ]
